'''Alan Hume''' ([[October 16]], [[1920s|1924]] - [[July 14]], [[2010]])<ref name="mi6" /> was a British cinematographer who worked as the director of photography for [[1983]]'s [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']].

His early credits as camera operator included [[Wikipedia:David Lean|David Lean's]] films and the comedy franchise [[Wikipedia:Carry On (franchise)|''Carry On'']], eventually serving as a regular director of photography in the 1960s. After ''Return of the Jedi'', Hume was the director of photography for several more films, including those of the ''James Bond'' franchise.

